  <text>
      <body>
         <div type="entry">
            <pb facs="https://leaf.bucknell.edu/sites/default/files/2026-01/diary11.jpg"/>
            <fw><placeName key="Camp Union"><placeName key="Camp Union" ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_gazetteer.xml#linnp0l14">Camp Union</placeName> </placeName>Near<placeName key="Annapolis, MD" ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_gazetteer.xml#linnpl002"> Annapolis Maryland</placeName></fw> <dateline>December <date>Monday 23. 1861</date>.</dateline>
            <p>We went to <persName key="Lt. Col. Potter" ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper097">Lieutenant Colonel Potters </persName><objectType key="tent">tent</objectType> &amp; heard <persName>Lieutenant Colonel Maggi</persName> read <persName key="Joseph Antoine Viguier De Monteil" ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper061">Lieutenant Colonel Viguier de Monteil's</persName> defence. It <name type="weather">rained</name> nearly all last night &amp; the greater part of the
               day. When I came back found the <objectType key="Camp Union">camp</objectType> in somewhat of an excitement, owing to the
               <objectType key="paymaster">paymaster</objectType> having arrived. <persName>Maj Morill </persName>and his assistant <persName>Mr Morton</persName>. As there were
               some errors we had ours to make over - or rather for them as they had made most of
               the mistakes.</p>
         </div>
